Questions:
Which aspect of the study is considered experimental for participants who have undergone radiation treatment for head and neck cancer?
A) Regular use of over-the-counter mouth sprays for hydration;
B) Comparison of two different over-the-counter mouth sprays to assess their effectiveness in treating dry mouth symptoms;
C) Routine pH testing of saliva to monitor acid levels in the mouth;
D) Completion of surveys regarding the effectiveness of standard dry mouth treatments.

Correct answer: B
